ZCZC EE57
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 032300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE IS CENTRED OVER THE UK AROUND 1035 WITH
LOW PRESSURE 988 CENTRED ACROSS NERN SCANDINAVIA. THE AZORES HIGH RIDGES
INTO THE S OF NITON AT THIS TIME WITH AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE ACROSS SERN
IBERIA. DURING THE PERIOD THE UK HIGH SINKS SWARDS INTO NERN FRANCE AND DECLINES
BUT REMAINS DOMINANT ACROSS THE AREA. BY SUNDAY ATLANTIC FRONTAL TROUGHS
ARE LIKELY TO ENCROACH INTO THE FAR W OR NW OF THE BRITISH ISLES. AN ATLANTIC
LOW IS EXP TO MOV INTO ROCKALL OR BAILEY MOV EWARDS BUT FLN IN THE NERN
N SEA DURING MONDAY. AT THE SAME TIME HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS ACROSS THE CONTINENT
WITH SLACK FLOW ACROSS MUCH OF NITON. OCNL STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY FRIDAY EVENING
ACROSS SHANNON AND IN THE S OF FITZROY ON SATURDAY EVENING AND EARLY SUNDAY.
OTHERWISE NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP FOR NITON DURING THE PERIOD
NNNN